# PREAMBLE

We, the founders and contributors of the Sindh Local Government Intelligence Framework (SLGIF), hereby establish this Constitution to ensure that every part of this project is developed in accordance with the Constitution of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan, the Sindh Local Government Act, 2013, and other applicable laws, rules, official notifications, and judicial precedents.

The primary objective of SLGIF is to build an independent, transparent, searchable, and legally reliable digital legal reference platform for Local Government institutions in Sindh.

This project is intended to assist Councillors, Chairmen, Vice Chairmen, Mayors, Deputy Mayors, Union Committee Chairmen, Municipal Officers, Government Departments, Lawyers, Researchers, Journalists, Students, and Citizens by providing structured legal information and guidance based upon authentic legal sources.

SLGIF shall never replace the law, the courts, or competent legal authorities. Artificial Intelligence within this project shall only assist users in understanding, locating, organizing, and drafting legal material. Every legal conclusion must remain subject to the original law and competent authority.

No legal provision, notification, amendment, judicial decision, quotation, or governmental instruction shall ever be fabricated, altered, or presented as authentic without verification from an official source.

Whenever any legal material is under review, unavailable, uncertain, or pending verification, such status shall be clearly disclosed to maintain transparency and public trust.

This Constitution establishes the permanent governance principles of the project and shall remain the highest governing document for every contributor, developer, editor, reviewer, and future Artificial Intelligence component integrated into SLGIF.

Project Motto:

**Law First — AI Second**

**Every Answer Backed by Law**
